[Course_Description]
Are you a learning professional looking to improve your development process and create better elearning? Elearning designer and author Tim Slade offers quick tips that can be immediately applied to your design process. Find out how to draft preliminary storyboards to explore your ideas, develop prototypes to test your functionality and visualize your look and feel, design more engaging and visually interesting courses, and add interactivity that gives learners a chance to practice and validate their skills. These tips are designed to be used by all elearning creators, regardless of the platform you create content on. Focus on the techniques that interest you, or use them in combination to save time and build a better end product for your learners.